  "elapsed_s": 5.2,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 41,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] So he actually went before the Kristallnacht.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 41,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "So therefore, it must have been somewhere around in August or September, he got the affidavit.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 41,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "He got a visa, and [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] he went off to America.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 42,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Not really.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 42,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "It was the decision of my parents that-- he was the middle brother-- that he must go.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 42,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And he was at the age, at that time, of 19-- 1938, yes, and he was 19.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 42,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "My older brother, who was a medical student, thought that he will be able-- was working on it-- that he will be able with the children transport to England.",
      "word_count": 29
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 42,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And that was because they were looking for people to accompany these children, and as he was a medical student it was possible that he will go.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 42,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] The-- [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] me, I queued up at many embassies, at many embassies, to try to find a-- to try to find a-- a country that would accept me as an immigrant.",
      "word_count": 38
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 42,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And I-- I went actually out to-- to, I remember, a Cuban embassy, Cuban embassy, Shanghai, countries I never heard of in South America and queued up sometimes all night long.",
      "word_count": 31
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 42,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "My parents said, look, the children, you must go.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 42,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "But nothing really-- we are too old-- nothing will happen to us.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 42,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "But you must create a new life outside the country.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 42,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "And I was not able to get a-- anywhere a visa, and [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] so I [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] didn't-- I wasn't able to go.",
      "word_count": 28
    }
  ],
